Finally,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  VI doesn't care that some 14 year old boy wants to copy a character to Test for pHAt lewt. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't want to play on test to just get the &quot;pHAt lewt&quot;, infact that is the least of my concerns. If people didn't have to play up a normal character to the higher levels to test out the higher level content the test server would be more viable for its primary job <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  TESTING </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. If people could alter their levels on the test server then you can be positive that EVERYTHING will be tested. Tell me, would you want to level up a character to 60? then another to 45, then another to 33, then another to 20 to test out all the differing content.<br>
<br>
Look at the idea in my first post there is an incentive to testing things, you would need to apply to it but that can try to filter all the &quot;pHAt lewt&quot; morons. And then the bill is cheapend because they are Verant's Guinea Pigs.<br>
